        "content": "I’ve completed the requested process:\n\n1. Created a temporary table `J09A_temp` from `decision_table` with all rows where `TOUR` starts with `J09A`.\n2. Added the column `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `J09A_temp`.\n3. Classified each house:\n   - Counted distinct `EQUNR` per `HAUS`.\n   - Applied overrides:\n     - `HOUSE_NUM1 = 0` → `EVU`\n     - `HOUSE_NUM1 BETWEEN 500 AND 599` → `EVU`\n     - `HOUSE_NUM1 BETWEEN 900 AND 999` → `EVU`\n   - Otherwise: `< 3` equipment → `KSA`, `>= 3` → `EVU`.\n4. Enriched with:\n   - `eablg` via `ANLAGE` = `Installation` to get `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`.\n   - `sales_master` and `net_master` via `EQUNR`.\n   - When both sales and net data exist, sales data is used; if only net exists, net data is used. (Implemented using `COALESCE(sales_master.col, net_master.col)`; this naturally falls back to net when sales is missing.)\n5. Exported the final result to CSV as `J09A.csv` with exactly these columns, in this order:\n   - `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`\n   - `HAUS`\n   - `ANLAGE`\n   - `ME_MA_ID`\n   - `EQUNR`\n   - `HOUSE_NUM1`\n   - `ENTSCHEIDUNG`\n   - `TITLE`\n   - `FORENAME`\n   - `SURNAME`\n   - `STREET`\n   - `STREETNO`\n   - `POST_CODE1`\n   - `CITY1`\n   - `CITY2`\n   - `EMAIL`\n6. Sent the CSV to `meter.readings@evu.com` with a short cover note.\n7. Dropped the temporary table `J09A_temp`.",
